    narr:generatedFrom "6411f91969dce364fb9b6ca3b27b856213fa0542" ;
    narr:narration """This hub documents the evolving orthographic and rhetorical conventions of the organization. While early observations emphasized a [code-adjacent, anti-corporate identity](narr:Position_LowercaseBrandStylization) signaled by [consistent lowercase](narr:StyleObs_AswrittenLowercase) usage, recent entries from June 2026 introduce a more nuanced [capitalization policy](narr:Position_AswrittenAICompanyized). This policy distinguishes between [body prose](narr:Position_AswrittenAICompanyized) (where 'Aswritten' is capitalized as a subject) and [technical references](narr:Position_AswrittenAICompanyized) (where URLs and email addresses remain lowercase), while reserving all-caps for the [wordmark](narr:Position_AswrittenAICompanyized). Beyond brand naming, the hub tracks a [systematic taxonomy of formatting](narr:StyleObs_BoldKeyTerms), including [backtick code spans](narr:StyleObs_BacktickToolNames) for system primitives, [all-caps conviction markers](narr:StyleObs_ConvictionLabel), and [provisional metadata flags](narr:StyleObs_AgentSim_ProvisionalFlag) used to manage research-branch status. The rhetorical register is defined by [staccato declarative fragments](narr:StyleObs_1) and [refraction-based metaphors](narr:StyleObs_1), creating a document style that functions as both technical documentation and a [dialogue-within-document](narr:StyleObs_1) experience.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Observation_AswrittenCapQuote> ;
